A third development lay in the way law and institutions were bent to protect allies and punish opponents. Attorney General Bondi directed the DOJ to drop charges mid-trial against Dr. Michael Kirk Moore, accused of destroying COVID vaccines and issuing fake vaccination cards, framing him as someone who had given patients \'93a choice.\'94 At the same time, the department sought only a one-day sentence for Brett Hankison, the former officer convicted of violating Breonna Taylor\'92s civil rights by firing into her bedroom during a botched raid, and a state court in Pennsylvania sentenced another officer to probation for killing a bystander outside a Walmart. These lenient responses to law enforcement and anti-vaccine actors contrasted sharply with the severity of immigration enforcement and with the treatment of lower-status offenders. Law was not being applied with one standard.\
